Wyman-Gordon Inc said it plansto invest 11.7 mln dlrs in two projects to improve thecompany's metals technology capabilities.    The projects include the installation of a plasma coldhearth refining system in its Millbury facility for theproduction of nickel-base alloy power metal and titanium alloyelectrodes, the company said.    The other involves the modification of its 35,000-tonhydraulic forging press, Wyman-Gordon said.    Both projects are scheduled for completion in 1989, thecompany said. Reuter&#3;